**6- Arrival time, required time and slack of all gates:**

\

Required arrival time (RAT) is calculated by setting the last node in
the graphs to tc (or tc-setup in sequential logic) and propagating
backwards and picking the lowest required time possible.

\

Actual arrival time (AAT) is calculated by starting from the input nodes
and checking the delays and take the worst arrival time of a path to be
saved in calculation of AAT of the next nodes

\

Slack is calculated by RAT - AAT for each node in the graphs
